                "actions": {
                    "value": ""
                },
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>After spending 1 minute in contact with a @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Paralyzed]{Paralyzed}, @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Unconscious]{Unconscious}, or willing creature, a totenmaske can reshape the target's face, causing flesh to cover vital features.</p>\n<p>The target can attempt a <span data-pf2-check=\"fortitude\" data-pf2-dc=\"25\" data-pf2-traits=\"curse,divine,necromancy\" data-pf2-label=\"Shape Flesh DC\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">Fortitude</span> save to resist; a critical success grants temporary immunity to Shape Flesh for 24 hours.</p>\n<p>Each time the totenmaske Shapes Flesh, it chooses one feature: ears (target becomes @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Deafened]{Deafened}), eyes (target becomes @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Blinded]{Blinded}), mouth (target can't speak or eat), or nose (target can't smell). A creature with both its nose and mouth sealed can't breathe and begins to suffocate.</p>\n<p>Changes are permanent until reversed by removing this curse, or the sealed flesh can be surgically opened with a <span data-pf2-check=\"medicine\" data-pf2-dc=\"25\" data-pf2-label=\"Shape Flesh DC\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">Medicine</span> check that takes [[/r 1d4 #rounds]] rounds and deals [[/r 1d6 #slashing]] slashing damage per round.</p>"
                },
